A cancer sufferer travelled thousands of miles across China to buy a two-legged goat that walks on its hind legs because he admires its strong spirit.

Wang Xinmin, who suffers from lymphoma, journeyed from his hometown in Fuyang in eastern China's Anhui Province to buy the animal for 4,500 Yuan (£450) in Zhoukou in Henan Province.

The 31-year-old made the decision after reading a newspaper report about how the goat had taught itself to walk after being born with only two hind legs.

